chart_description: This chart shows the amount of time (in milliseconds) a task waits due to I/O pressure on some type of storage device. I/O pressure happens when the operating system tries to allocate more than the available resources of a device or file system, causing it to stall and increase the task wait time.

dimension_descriptions.some 10: This dimension represents the I/O stall time for tasks that waited 10-20% of the observed time.
dimension_descriptions.some 300: This dimension represents the I/O stall time for tasks that waited 200-300% of the observed time.
dimension_descriptions.some 60: This dimension represents the I/O stall time for tasks that waited 50-60% of the observed time.
